title: Independent Candidate Athar Maqbool wins PP-279 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 10 (APP): Independent Candidate, Muhammad Athar Maqbool has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-279, Layyah-I by securing 54,423 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Malik Ahmed Ali Lakkh of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) who bagged 51,478 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 57.65%.
